May 3 2007 	Great Hotel Great Location	I stayed at the City Suites for two nights (April 20 and 21) and had a wonderful time. Taking the red line train from downtown, the hotel conveniently located just a couple steps away from the station. It was great to be able to get off the train and be in the hotel within minutes. In the afternoons, there are fresh cookies and fruit in the lobby, which was a nice surprise.The elevator is TINY. I don't think I have ever been in such a small elevator in my life. Since there were a group of us staying there, we found it faster, easier and much less claustrophobic to just take the stairs. not a big deal at all. All rooms have free wireless internet! This was very convenient for planning our outings over the weekend, as well as for doing online check-in for our flights home.We actually had three different room types reserved for our group, so I got to see a variety of what the hotel offers:The first night I stayed in a small suite with 2 double beds, a bathroom,and a small sitting area that had a couch and desk. The couch pulled out into a full size bed. The room was very clean when we arrived, the beds were comfortable. We were on the non-train side of the building, so it was also very quiet. The room had a small fridge, which was convenient. My only complaint with this room was that in order to flush the toilet, you had to hold down the handle until it was done.The second night I stayed in a large king suite with an adjoining standard queen room. The queen room was very small - just a bed and a bathroom. The kind suite was very large - a very spacious sitting area with couch, chair, table and chairs, as well as a tv, fridge, and microwave. The king bed was in a separate area and had a door so that the sleeping and living area were two separate rooms. Both the queen room and king suite were very nice and clean. my only complaint with these rooms again dealt with plumbing - the shower was very slow to drain. But the building is very old and you almost have to expect some issues with plumbing...and it was nothing to really complain about. Even though these two rooms were on the train side of the building, I didn't think it wasn't as big a problem as other reviewers have made it out to be. Yes, during the day when you're awake the train is definitely noticeable and somewhat loud. But I laid down in bed, fell asleep, and didn't notice the train again until I woke up the next day. Maybe it wasn't a problem for me since I grew up near train tracks, and I currently live near a hospital with constant sirens and helicopters? But if you think it will be a problem, just request a room on the other side of the building and you'll barely be able to hear the train.Continental breakfast was free in the lobby, consisting of yogurt, fruit cups, hot pockets, etc. It was nice to have (especially if you're in a hurry), but I would highly recommend skipping the continental breakfast and walking across the street to the 24 hour diner. We ate their twice during our stay, and the food and service was excellent both times.The hotel is within easy walking distance of many bars, stores, and Wrigley Field. And if you're heading into the city, the train station is right next door so you can very quickly and easily get wherever you need to go.The front desk requests that you check out of your room by 11am, but we were running a little late and after calling the desk, they had no problem giving us an extra hour and letting us check out at noon. Even better, since we didn't need to leave for the airport for another 3 hours, they were nice enough to let us store our luggage in a locked room near the front desk while we went out to lunch so we wouldn't have to carry it around with us.I would definitely recommend staying at the City Suites Hotel - it's a very nice hotel in a very convenient location.	
