d to dope up on allergy pills to try to deal with it. He is also an early riser and was looking forward to the &quot;free continental breakfast&quot; that was promised from 7am-11am, while he did work and waited for me. He went down at 7am and there was not only no food - but not even anyone at the desk or in the lobby to help. He went back again about 45min later and there was still no one and no food. When we left the hotel around 10am we finally saw a few donuts and cereal. Similarly, we were told there would be complimentary evening cookies between 4-8pm. The second day we were there we happened to be coming back around 5pm and thought cookies and tea sounded nice. Again, though, no cookies. When I went to ask the front desk agent, I found her with her head down asleep behind a partition. She said the cookies would be out &quot;later&quot;.We also found the housekeeping to be very poor. We know they came the second day because our bed was made and our tip was gone. But they did not refresh any of the toiletries (even though they were almost out), did not put anything away or tidy up, and seemed to have not cleaned, vacuumed or washed anything but the bare essentials. I think they came in, made the bed, put out some fresh towels, grabbed the money and left. Clearly the entire hotel is designed to offer the littlest possible that it can get away with.If the price had been MUCH cheaper, I could understand staying at this hotel - it's adequate and a step up from a complete dump. But we will never stay here again and never recommend it. We walked by the Best Western and it looked a lot nicer, I'm assuming the inside can't be any worse than City Suites. If you have an option, I think you're better off looking for a deal on a downtown hotel (they all have to compete because there are so many, so you get a LOT more class, better staff, nicer rooms, etc.) and walking/driving/taking &quot;el&quot; or anything else to get up to Lakeview.	
