Jul 20 2005 	Adorable comfortable room. Good value	My daughter and I came to look at a few colleges in Chicago. We just needed a decent room in a convenient location. This hotel more than met our expectations.We were a little surprised when we found the hotel was 2 shops from the El station, but we never heard any train noise. We arrived at 6am, and the hotel let us check in early. We had only reserved a &quot;room&quot; not a suite, and they gave us a discount when me mentioned we were touring Loyola.I think they upgraded us. Our room was like a junior suite...bedroom with 2 twins, a TV, desk and 2 nightstands. The &quot;living room&quot; had no door but had a loveseat/bed, an easy chair, table and another TV. All the furniture was light wood and looked pretty new. The bathroom was classic 1930s- small tiles on the floor, white subway wall tiles- looked straight from Restoration Hardware! The best was that the floor was heated! Felt so nice! They allowed us to eat breakfast on our arrival as well as departure date- nothing fancy...Tea, coffee, fruits and pastries.All in all, we were very happy here. My only complaint was that the desk clerk told me it would take 30 minutes on the El to get to the airport at 6 am. It was closer to an hour, and we almost missed our flight!!	
Jun 21 2005	Shabby hotel in shabby neighborhood	The best thing I can say about this place is that it's steps from an El station, so that a quick trip to the Loop area is no problem. Unfortunately, that also means that you can hear the El rumbling every few munites in the day and throughout the night. The room we had was spacious but shabby, not at all what I had imagined from the pictures on the Internet. My companion had stayed a few nights before in a fine Chicago hotel for about the same price, so she was especially unimpressed. Some muight regard the neighborhood as funky and happening (restaurants, nightclubs), but dirty and shabby are equally apt (--- shops, street people). In view of recommendations from well-known travel guides, this place was a real disappointment.	
May 18 2005	Location a huge asset	We stayed at City Suites for 4 nights. Our room was clean, quiet, and roomy. The convenience of the El only a few doors down is great, as is having the Halsted nightlife only a couple of blocks away. Great Chicago pizza and hot dogs nearby. The staff was helpful and friendly- Russ went above and beyond with his guidance on dining and entertainment for our stay. Coffee and tea are available throughout the day and evening. I have stayed here in the past and it will be my only choice next time as well.	
May 11 2005	Not a luxury hotel but still good	If you think you're going to find a true suite in Chicago for $164/night, you're dreaming. Having said that, our &quot;pseudo&quot; king suite (see prior review) was quite adequate for my spouse, toddler &amp; me. We needed to be in that eclectic neighborhood (GREAT Vietnamese restuarant and a few tattoo parlors) for a family event, but it's certainly convenient to the traditional attractions without the &gt;$200/night price tag for a shoebox on the Mag Mile. Speaking of which, ANY hotel within 150 yards of an El station isn't going to be quiet. Our room overlooked the front entrance, but we were able to ignore the hub-bub (and our home is in the middle of 200 acres of undeveloped land).I agree that there was a snippy male manager, but the remainder of the staff was very gracious. The 24/7 fresh fruit and tea was nice, but skip the breakfast. There are plenty of good eats just steps from the hotel. The room would definitely be cramped for a family of four, but then so would most rooms. It's no Four Seasons, but we would stay there again.	
May 8 2005	one room does not make a siute	My wife and I stayed at City Suites Saturday May 7, 2005. We reserved a &quot;King Suite&quot; which was purported to be a suite with a fold out couch bed. We needed a suite so that our daughter in law could use it while we could maintain or privacy. In fact the room was not a &quot;suite&quot; at all, just a room with a half wall between a seating area and a king bed. No privacy at all.  I espressed my concerns to the on duty manager Ross. Ross told me in a very rude and condescending manner that If I hadn't booked the room on &quot;Cheap hotels Dot Com&quot; I would have known that the room was not a &quot;suite&quot; but really a &quot;Junior Suite.&quot; He then told me that he was canceling our reservation and was giong to find us a &quot;real suite that will cost your ------ $500.00.&quot; If he were my employee he would be immediately fired.Ther web page, which I referred to before I CALLED and asked numerous questions before I made reservations at the link provided intimates that City Suites Hotel does indeed have suites. El noise all night long and lousy continental breakfast, not worth the price.	
May 2 2005	A good hotel in a great location	We stayed at the City Suites on Saturday, April 30th for one night. We booked a standard queen room (not a suite) since we were not planning on spending much time in the room. The room was a bit larger than most boutique hotels in a city. The bathroom had a bit more room as well. We had no problem with noise as mentioned in other posts. The room was very quite.The best asset of this hotel is the location. We came in for a concert and wanted to bar hop on Halsted after the show. This hotel is perfect as Halsted is only a block away. There are also plenty of shops and good restaurants nearby. There is a train station right next door which makes getting around the city easy.Overall the hotel is a good value.	
Jan 9 2005	Paper thin walls	We got a decent price for out hotel room so I can't complain about that. The rooms were a bit small but nicely decorated and clean. I really liked the hotel for its location and style. The only problem we had was the paper thin walls. After celebrating all night we only wanted a good sleep before driving back to the suburbs in the morning. All we heard was a baby crying through out the night, people talking in their rooms, and footsteps constantly in the hallway. I would not recommend this hotel to anyone for that reason. I would reconsider if they renovated with some sound proofing.	
Dec 12 2004	I LOVE THIS HOTEL!!	I have been staying at City Suites hotel every year for the past 8 years, when my friends and I come at the end of June for the exciting parade weekend in &quot;Boys-Town&quot; Chicago.The hotel is perfect, comfortable, convenient to all the areas we like to visit, including our favourite health club, which is within walking distance of the hotel!The staff is always helpful and friendly. Even one year, they had a water main break on the day of our arrival, and they put my entire party (of 6 people) up in the Quality Inn, on Michigan Ave., just for one night, totally free of charge, including dinner and cocktails, as well as crediting our first night at City Suites!Restaurants, shopping, night-clubs, all within walking distance, as well as the conventient &quot;El&quot; station right outside the hotel doors!I recommend this hotel to everyone!	
Oct 12 2004	Nice old building	I loved the location because it was away from downtown and very close to where I wanted to be. My son and I shared a double suite and the room was small. I liked the feel of the old building, and the bathroom was kind of art deco, but there were no counter tops, and very little space to put &quot;stuff.&quot; For the amount I paid, I would have liked to have a larger bed, and glasses instead of plastic cups, a closer ice machine (1 machine located on the lobby floor.) The building is old but quaint. The elevator is slow, and the floors creak. The lighting is dim. There are cealing fans in both rooms and air conditioning window units. I had no view-just bricks from the building next door. The room was very quiet. I did not hear the &quot;El&quot; or any outside noise. A continental breakfast was served each day with bagels, muffins, juice, cereal, coffee and teas. If you know that it is an old building and you like that, then it is charming. It was not bad or terrible, just that it wasn't anything special. I probably would not stay here again if I didn't have to.	
